Iavan Pijoos, News24Cigarettes (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The Soweto Flying Squad recovered a hijacked truck carrying cigarettes after a shoot-out with three suspects in Diepkloof, Johannesburg on Thursday, police said.The flying squad was patrolling in Zone Five in Diepkloof when they were told to be on the look-out for the hijacked truck, Lieutenant Kay Makhubela said.Makhubela said a shoot-out ensued when police spotted the truck.One suspect was shot and taken to hospital under police custody.Two other suspects managed to escape.None of the police officers were injured.&nbsp;A case of hijacking and attempted murder was opened.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.